This is an action RPG boss battle. Avoid the enemy's attacks
and attack with the A key. While holding the D key, you can
move while keeping your direction fixed.

If either your stamina or health reaches zero from the
enemy's attacks, you will be defeated. Generally, ranged
attacks reduce health, and contact reduces stamina.

When you come into contact with the enemy, you will be held
and continue to take damage until you succeed at the timing
bar. Let me show you the timing bar.

Stopping on yellow is a success, stopping on red is a
critical. If you stop on yellow, you take damage and are
released, while stopping on red reduces the damage by half
and you are released.

Furthermore, taking damage to your stamina from the enemy
will put you in a \C[14]state of arousal\C[0], reducing the
number of slashes during your attack. A heart mark will
appear on your status during arousal.

Arousal can be removed by walking around a certain number of
steps. It is also removed if you achieve a critical to shake
off the hold. If possible, aim to stop on red.

Learn the enemy's attack patterns. The enemy's attacks have
patterns. Focus on avoiding them first to learn them.

Make use of the D key's direction lock. Locking your
direction makes it easier to attack and evade. Attacking
while backing away can make the fight easier.

Use healing items and skills. There are no usage limits for
healing items and skills (such as deep breathing). It's
possible to heal and push through aggressively.

Use the Action Ease option. Turning on Action Ease from the
options will significantly lower the difficulty level. There
are no downsides.
